{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can generate documentation using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/apple.github.io\/swift-docc-plugin\/documentation\/swiftdoccplugin\/"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can also read a current version of this documentation online"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/rhx.github.io\/SwiftGtk4Doc\/"}]},{"anchor":"Documentation-Structure","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Documentation Structure"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The documentation structure for SwiftGtk follows the structure of the generated Swift source files."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For every "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object"},{"type":"text","text":", there is a Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swift-book\/documentation\/the-swift-programming-language\/protocols\/"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that provides a default implementation of the Object’s methods and properties."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For the documentation, the use of Protocols means that the methods and properties"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are usually documented in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Default Implementations"},{"type":"text","text":" Section towards the bottom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rather than the main section of the type documentation."}]},{"style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can quickly navigate to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Default Implementations"},{"type":"text","text":" Section"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by clicking on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Relationships"},{"type":"text","text":" link in the navigation column"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the right hand side."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Tip"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are two concrete types that wrap the Object in Swift and inherit the protocol implementation:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ref"},{"type":"text","text":" type (named after the type with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ref"},{"type":"text","text":" suffix)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that simply provides a typed wrapper around the underlying C language pointer."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This type is typically returned by methods, functions, or properties that reference already"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"existing instances of a given Object, e.g. a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/Gtk\/MenuModelRef"},{"type":"text","text":" returned by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/Application\/menubar"},{"type":"text","text":" property or a list ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/GLib\/RefList"},{"type":"text","text":") of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/WindowRef"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returned by the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/Application\/windows"},{"type":"text","text":" property."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Memory management for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ref"},{"type":"text","text":" instances uses the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk"},{"type":"text","text":" mechanisms, which in most"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cases means that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/GLibObject\/ref"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/GLibObject\/unref"},{"type":"text","text":" calls need to be used for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference counting and manual memory management."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"a class type (named after the type without a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ref"},{"type":"text","text":" suffix)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that provides a full Swift class implementation of the type."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For most Objects this means that memory is fully managed through Swift’s [automatic reference counting]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swift-book\/documentation\/the-swift-programming-language\/automaticreferencecounting\/)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"mechanism."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, the documentation for the methods provided by "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/Window"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be found in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/WindowProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" article.  The same is true for "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/WindowRef"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Using-DocC","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Using DocC"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To preview documentation matching your local installation, simply run"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["swift 